text: @onewomanoneday heading home for christmas and just took in a no nonsense podcast with baroness helena kennedy qc. it struck me that on two occasions this year, i have heard two highly accomplished women : stella creasy and now baroness kennedy who have the guts to say it as it is.  part of me recoils slightly - we have been conditioned to beware outspoken women but most of me asks how do we take the conversation mainstream without alienating more conservative forces.  kennedy rifted on many topics including the demise of the professions - you are only successful as a lawyer if you make money, meaning many talented students stay clear of low paying crime or legal aid cases but both she and creasy spoke bluntly about how our systems are failing women and why self regulation is not sufficient; we need processes of accountability because without them women wonâ€™t speak about abuse, harassment, sexism for fear of being the troublesome one.  the air is so tense  since #metoo - we have millennials and the generations after who are used to information and transparency : the old way of burying our head in the sand and letting it blow away will not cut it if organisations public or private want to recruit and retain the best talent.  we oldies need to take it upon ourselves to encourage a culture that talks about the hard stuff even if we canâ€™t always change it. #baronesskennedy #stellacreasy #metoo

text:
when i was four, my gymnastics coach passed a comment about how â€œcuteâ€ my ass looked. my mother overheard him, and had to fight with the management to have him fired.
when i was twelve, i felt a hand slip under my t-shirt as i was leaving a movie hall. there was too much of a crowd to move away. i felt it on my stomach, felt as it moved to my breast, and squeezed. i tried to pry it away, but he was too strong. i felt ashamed for some reason, and didnâ€™t mention it to anyone. i wondered if i was at fault for wearing a fitting t-shirt. maybe i should have worn a kurta. 
when i was sixteen, i was walking to math tuitions before school one morning. a man rode his bike close to me and grabbed my breast. before i could realise what had happened, he sped away. the very next day, he was back again, only to yell, â€œi want to fuck you!â€ and speed away again. i was in my school uniform both times. to this day, i avoid walking those streets. 
my body has been sexualized and objectified my entire life. these are just some of the incidents. which one do you want to talk about?
.
.
apart from the indian penal code, children under the age of 18 are protected by the protection of children from sexual offences act (pocso), 2012. .
.
child sexual abuse (csa) is a mental or physical violation of a child with sexual intent, generally by a person who is in the position of power and trust of a child. 
apart from the definition, sexual abuse also includes an adult who touches the childâ€™s genital organ with hands or with other objects and persuading the child to touch their genitalia i.e. touching and fondling of a child.

#metoo #standagainstharassment #reclaimthestreets #fightsexualharassment #endviolenceagainstwomen #standup4humanrights #timesup #humanrights #unwomen #unwomenindia

"she was quite controlling, she always used to take my money out of my bank account when i got paid," says "dean". "she threw stuff at me. she basically kept me away from my family for the last 10 years." in the age of #metoo, it's very easy to forget (and very important to remember) that men can be victims of abuse, domestic violence, sexual assault, rape and other types of abuse as well. 
these are problems plaguing all genders and it's important to address this issue can impact literally anyone. 'dean' (whose name has been changed to protect his identity) tells his terrible story of suffering:  https://bbc.in/2guczo0

text:
a few months later, in autumn 2013, wylie met steve bannon. at the time, he was editor-in-chief of breitbart, which he had brought to britain to support his friend nigel farage in his mission to take britain out of the european union.

what was he like? - smart, says wylie. - interesting. really interested in ideas. heâ€™s the only straight man iâ€™ve ever talked to about intersectional feminist theory. he saw its relevance straightaway to the oppressions that conservative, young white men feel.

wylie meeting bannon was the moment petrol was poured on a flickering flame. wylie lives for ideas. he speaks 19 to the dozen for hours at a time. he had a theory to prove. and at the time, this was a purely intellectual problem. politics was like fashion, he told bannon.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
a few months later, in autumn 2013, wylie met steve bannon. at the time, he was editor-in-chief of breitbart, which he had brought to britain to support his friend nigel farage in his mission to take britain out of the european union.

what was he like? - smart, says wylie. - interesting. really interested in ideas. heâ€™s the only straight man iâ€™ve ever talked to about intersectional feminist theory. he saw its relevance straightaway to the oppressions that conservative, young white men feel.

wylie meeting bannon was the moment petrol was poured on a flickering flame. wylie lives for ideas. he speaks 19 to the dozen for hours at a time. he had a theory to prove. and at the time, this was a purely intellectual problem. politics was like fashion, he told bannon.

mainly because i need to get out of my own head, stop thinking about me + think about who else i could help from my own experience...ğŸ™
.
you see, last week, only 2 days after being in the magical desert of nevada usağŸŒµand after 20 years of living with the emotional scars, i fronted in court to stand up to the person who sexually abused me over + over as a child. the most hurtful part was, he was found not guilty due to a technicality in the legislation ğŸ’”
.
insert: total devastation, continued feelings of unworthiness + feeling completely disempowered. it literally buckled me with physical + emotional pain for 2 days straight. i cried. i got angry. i slept for 16 hours. i struggled to be a mum or even a live human ğŸ˜¥
.
but you know what? i had to go through that process (unattached to the result) to prove to myself that i had done everything in my power to bring him to justice + to allow myself to fully let go + let the magic of my real life unfold ğŸ’« a life that is not suffocated by all the pain + secrets!
.

.
trust me, it will not serve you to bottle it up,Â  suppress it or drown it with drugs, alcohol or other means - been there, done that! ğŸ¤¦â€â™€ï¸ yes, it's scary as shit + hard as hell. but there is a new light at the end of the tunnel that is way prettier that any light you've seen before ğŸŒˆ
.

text:
good morning saints! the bible says: "he that dwelleth in the secret place of the most high shall abide under the shadow of the almighty." psalms 91:1 kjv. to dwell in god's secret places, you must have a zeal to search them out. they are called secret places for a reason. right now, as we are fleshly beings we are constantly living in the valley of the shadow of death. but once we connect with the almighty god and crave his word and stay in his face, god reveals more and more of himself to us. the shadow of death is no longer a hindrance because we have accepted protection under the shadow of the almighty! so today search out a secret place of god! amen!

good morning saints! there is a big difference in working hard for the church and working hard for god. we can't get so caught up in the business of "church work," that we forget about the god that it's suppose to be for. the love that jesus displayed is the example of love we should have for one another. don't allow your love to be lost because you found business! jesus says: â€œi know your works, your toil and your patient endurance, and how you cannot bear with those who are evil, but have tested those who call themselves apostles and are not, and found them to be false. i know you are enduring patiently and bearing up for my name's sake, and you have not grown weary. but i have this against you, that you have abandoned the love you had at first. remember therefore from where you have fallen; repent, and do the works you did at first. if not, i will come to you and remove your lampstand from its place, unless you repent.â€ revelationâ€¬ â€­2:2-5â€¬ â€­esvâ€¬â€¬. don't lose your place in heaven because you became too busy for his love!!

text:

text:
good morning saints! 
revelation knowledge: we have two foster kids, both are 1 years old. and all they like to do is sit and watch us. they do this for hours if we let them. but soon as we say go play with your toys they walk off crying! it's so weird...lol. this happens off and on all day. so this morning right after breakfast they got down out of their chairs and sat on the couch and just stared at us while we ate and even when we finished they just sat their content as can be. we said go play with your toys and they walked off crying again. i told my wife i just don't get it. and in that same instance god says o me, "how would you feel if i made you leave my presents?" wow!!! this is why god wants us to have an understanding heart! the anointing on our lives draw people in and we must pray to god to understand why they are there and understand that they want to be in the presents of god like you. they may not know how to come to god but they know you! amen!

text:
good morning saints! â€œi will bless the lord at all times; his praise shall continually be in my mouth.â€
â€­â€­psalmsâ€¬ â€­34:1â€¬ â€­esvâ€¬â€¬. how do we bless the lord? when we bless one another we are either encouraged or helped in some way naturally or spiritually. but as we bless god we do not encourage nor do we help god in any way. when blessing the lord, we do it through thanks and praise! i bless the lord becomes "i thank the lord" and or "i praise the lord at all times!" and as i thank and praise him, it will continually be in my mouth! all true blessings comes from god so when we see a scripture that says "blessed be the lord," it's only fitting that the lord must be blessed because he is the originator of where true blessings come from! blessing the lord is to praise, thank, honor and give glory to the one and only living god that freed us from bondage and blesses us on a daily basis just because he loves us that much! amen!

text:
good morning saints! â€œthe lord will fight for you, and you have only to be silent." exodusâ€¬ â€­14:14â€¬ â€­esvâ€¬â€¬. moses was on holy ground at the burning bush. as long as he was in the presents of god nothing could harm him naturally or spiritually. god told moses to take of his shoes and he did. from then on he was protected while he was in the presence of the lord. during the plagues, and leaving egypt, god told the children of israel to do specific things and they followed them to the letter and they made it out without going to war. our god is the god of peace! we are not fighting people we are fighting spirits within people. which means you are fighting things we are not capable of fighting without the help of the lord. we really need to stay in the face of god, be obedient to his word and become that holy place were he resides and watch how far he removes egypt from you, amen!

text:
â€œbut seek first the kingdom of god and his righteousness, and all these things will be added to you." matthewâ€¬ â€­6:33â€¬ â€­esvâ€¬â€¬. our walk as christians is about kingdom living. this is the spiritual way to live a natural life. but sometimes we tend to live our natural lives by natural means. we have to stop allowing our circumstances to dictate our life. and allow your spiritual life style in christ to conquer your circumstances. seeking the kingdom means to study the kingdom. understand the god you serve. live a kingdom life. follow the precepts that god has given you through the work of his son, jesus christ. and be the kingdom. allow the kingdom of god to shine in you and through you for all take notice. the desires of our heart is different from our desires of the flesh. the things that will be added unto us are the necessary things for survival as human beings according to our level of faith and god's will. seeking the kingdom first before all things is key to the prosperity of freedom we have in christ jesus! amen!

text:
good afternoon saints! â€œif we confess our sins, he is faithful and just to forgive us our sins, and to cleanse us from all unrighteousness.â€ 1 johnâ€¬ â€­1:9â€¬ â€­kjvâ€¬â€¬. owning up to your faults and asking for forgiveness is major maturity in your walk with christ! we have to stop playing the blame game and own up to our part in things that go wrong in our lives. confession to god is freedom from sin. as long as you blame others for your short comings, you can never be freed from the bondage of self! to understand the righteousness of god is to first understand the wrong that lies within ourselves. the bible says: â€œand be found in him, not having mine own righteousness, which is of the law, but that which is through the faith of christ, the righteousness which is of god by faith:â€ philippiansâ€¬ â€­3:9â€¬ â€­kjvâ€¬â€¬. our way is not the right way but god's way is the only way. and that way is through his son, jesus christ! amen!

text:
good morning saints! â€œshe will bear a son, and you shall call his name jesus, for he will save his people from their sins." matthewâ€¬ â€­1:21â€¬ â€­esvâ€¬â€¬. it's amazing that the living god we serve saves us from ourselves. we have shortcomings that we can't handle alone. we have problems that we can't solve by ourselves. we think sometimes that we can run our lives without god involved and that is road leading to destruction. the bible says: â€œin all thy ways acknowledge him, and he shall direct thy paths.â€ proverbsâ€¬ â€­3:6â€¬ â€­kjvâ€¬â€¬. the acknowledgment is important because without it, you don't recognize he's there nor do you here his voice. too much of yourself is in the way and now your journey is in darkness. the sins of man have been conquered by the son of god on the cross! now there is no excuse for walking in darkness. turn the light on within you and walk with the savior of the world jesus christ! amen!

text:
good afternoon saints!  sharing a revelation thought: 
jesus was born in a place that wasnâ€™t his (luke 2:7). he was laid in a tomb that wasnâ€™t his own (matthew 27:59-60). jesus was wrapped in swaddling clothes when he was born (luke 2:12). in birth, angels proclaimed jesus had  come into the world (luke 2:9-12). in death, angels also proclaimed jesus had risen from the dead (luke 24:4-7). in birth, shepherd men proclaim the christ child was born (luke 2:17-19). in death, mary magdalene & other women proclaimed the christ has risen (luke 24:10). in birth, the wisemen brought gifts to jesus (matthew 2:11-12). in death, jesus rose from the dead and gave us the gift of the holy spirit and a chance at everlasting life (1 corinthians 15:3-4; john 3:16)! these were just a few things i found interesting as jesus was born, died and resurrected.  our savior was born into a natural existence to save our souls for an everlasting spiritual life. awesome!

text:
a few months later, in autumn 2013, wylie met steve bannon. at the time, he was editor-in-chief of breitbart, which he had brought to britain to support his friend nigel farage in his mission to take britain out of the european union.

what was he like? - smart, says wylie. - interesting. really interested in ideas. heâ€™s the only straight man iâ€™ve ever talked to about intersectional feminist theory. he saw its relevance straightaway to the oppressions that conservative, young white men feel.

wylie meeting bannon was the moment petrol was poured on a flickering flame. wylie lives for ideas. he speaks 19 to the dozen for hours at a time. he had a theory to prove. and at the time, this was a purely intellectual problem. politics was like fashion, he told bannon.

the guardian
